We are trying to make Morning Leap more convenient for parents. You can either sign up for the week and pay your $10 or pay $2 a day and use it when needed! We would like you to prepay for the week or month if you know you are coming each day. Otherwise pay daily- if Not paid we will send home a bill on Fridays.

post_text:
We're Hiring Childcare Provider
Approximately 32 Hours

Job Description
We provide childcare for infants-preschool. Must be at least 16 years old, love children, pass a background check, and be reliable. Experience with children preferred, but not required.

To Apply
Employment applications are located on the Andrew School District Website under Employment Opportunities.

Applications can be submitted to Andrea Kuhlman @ Andrea.kuhlman@Andrew.k12.ia.us or they can be dropped off at the elementary office in Andrew. In the subject line, please write Andrew vacancy.

post_text:
Hi there! I hope everyone's official summer is off to a great start, in this crazy season we are in. I wanted to share with everyone that I will be taking a new position next year at Briggs Elementary. It was a heart wrenching decision as Andrew has always been my home and I feel very honored to serve our students here.

I'm so proud of all of the amazing things our school has accomplished in the past decade, and I know these amazing things will continue.

Thank you everyone for your love, support, and friendships.

As Always, I love your face! ü•∞

post_text:
Students from 4th, 5th and 6th grade represented the Andrew Talented and Gifted program at the 13th Annual QCESC Battle of the Bridges competition at the Putnam Museum on Friday. Teams were challenged to build a lightweight bridge that could sustain a large amount of weight. The most efficient bridges and most intuitive designs were celebrated.

Our students performed well! All three teams placed within the top four of most efficient bridges. A huge congratulations to our sixth graders for being awarded the FIRST place trophy for the most efficient bridge in the elementary team pool!

The students and Mr. Riedesel agree it was an amazing first experience for our school and that they can‚Äôt wait to go back next year. Go Hawks!!

post_text: At the recommendation of the governor of Iowa, Andrew CSD will be closed for a minimum of four weeks. Effective March 17, only essential staff will be able to access the school. Staff PD will be held as scheduled for March 16. If you need any student belongings, etc please gather them from school tomorrow. We are working on plans to offer options for learning at home, meals for students, and more. We will communicate additional details as soon as possible. We urge you to practice social distancing as much as possible to protect the elderly and those with other health issues. Remember, we are a school family and we will get through this together. Take Care.

post_text: Dear Andrew Community, The Andrew administration is continuing to work with all our partners to determine the best course of action to best respond to the coronavirus threat. No decisions have been made but there is a strong chance that extended school closures will occur, even as early as Tuesday of this week. Please coordinate plans with your family to prepare for any changes in our school schedule. We will keep you posted ASAP with any new developments. Take Care!

post_text: Before break we sent out information about how the number of free/reduced price lunch students affects our school funding. Currently, the future of our after school program is in jeopardy if more Andrew CSD families do not accept the assistance they qualify for. This is the last chance to apply in order to help our school qualify for the funding to offer before/after school LEAP and more. To apply, please download the form at https://www.benefits.gov/benefit/1965 or ask Carla in the Andrew school office. Thanks!
